sample_rows.abstract_localized:
[
  {
    "language": "en",
    "text": "The two-stage process is for drying and conditioning expandable styrene polymers (EPS) obtained by suspension polymerisation in presence of blowing agent, followed by separation on a centrifuge to give EPS with a residual moisture content of ca. 2% and an average particle diameter of 0.1-3.0 mm. The process comprises : (a) passing the EPS (1) through a drier (2) with a first gas stream (3) with a temperature of 20-40 degrees C, a gas/EPS ratio of 1.3-1.9 kg/kg and a residence time of 0.05-0.2 minutes then separating the EPS from the gas, and (b) contacting the EPS in a second drier (7) with a second gas stream (8) at 20-40 degrees C, with a residence time of 240-480 minutes from product inlet to outlet and a gas/EPS ratio of 0.15-0.6 kg/kg, and with the gas flow in the same and/or opposite direction to the product flow, the gas being divided into different streams (9), fed into the EPS at different levels one above the other and re-dissipitated between these levels. Also claimed is an apparatus for t his process.",
    "truncated": false
  }
]

